{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionSince the publication of the seminal report on patient safety-To Err Is Human [1], the importance of preventing adverse events in health care has been widely recognized.",
    "Adverse events refer to unintended or unexpected incidents that occur during hospital care that cause harm to a patient [2].",
    "Common adverse events include complications, falls, and medication errors.",
    "These events can lead to prolonged hospital stays, permanent harm to patients, life-saving interventions, or even contributing to patient deaths [2,3].",
    "Unfortunately, adverse events remain one of the top 10 leading causes of death and disability worldwide, resulting in 251,454 deaths annually in the United States alone [4]."
  ],
